Lanka Offers Generous Incentives For Investors 
The Sri Lankan government has offered generous tax incentives to
investors to promote new investments in industries, services and
infrastructure, official sources said today.
Firms using advanced technologies and those that undertake large-scale
development projects will be granted a five year tax holiday and
exemption to dividends payable to shareholders.
They will also be able to import plant and machinery duty free and will
be exempted from turnover taxes for one year.
In the case of large scale investors, an extended tax holiday is
offered. Investments of 100 million US dollars will be entitled to a 10
year tax holiday. Investments of 500 million US dollars will be
entitled to a 12 year tax holiday while investments of 1,000 million US
dollars will be entitled to a 15 year tax holiday.
